ANSWER: To take an object as a parameter in an exposed web method, you need to define the web method with the appropriate input parameter type. For example:
```
@WebMethod(action = "createClaim")
public ClaimDTO createClaim(@WebParam(name = "claimDetails") ClaimDetails claimDetails) {
// Your implementation here
}
```
In this example, the `ClaimDetails` object is used as an input parameter for the `createClaim` web method.

